NextOS: guard <sys/sysctl.h> include for glibc 2.32+

glibc 2.32 (2020) removed the obsolete <sys/sysctl.h> header; the
sysctl(2) syscall has been deprecated by Linux in favor of /proc.
The Apple diskdev_cmds port still #includes it unconditionally in
makehfs.c, but nothing in the file actually calls sysctl() — it's
just a leftover from the Darwin original.

Fix: wrap the include in `#if !LINUX`, matching the style already
used for <sys/vmmeter.h> two lines below.

--- diskdev_cmds-332.14/newfs_hfs.tproj/makehfs.c	2006-02-20 22:45:15.000000000 +0100
+++ diskdev_cmds-332.14/newfs_hfs.tproj/makehfs.c	2026-04-24 14:00:00.000000000 +0000
@@ -37,7 +37,9 @@
 #endif
 #include <sys/errno.h>
 #include <sys/stat.h>
+#if !LINUX
 #include <sys/sysctl.h>
+#endif
 #if !LINUX
 #include <sys/vmmeter.h>
 #endif
